ThemeConfig Model

Overview
The ThemeConfig model manages theme configuration for the Comserv application. It handles loading theme definitions from JSON configuration files and provides site-specific theme selection with session caching.

Key Features
- Loads theme definitions from canonical JSON configuration file
- Maps site names to specific themes using site_themes configuration
- Provides session-based theme caching for performance
- Handles fallback to default theme when no mapping exists
- Comprehensive error handling and logging
- Case-insensitive site name matching

Methods

get_theme_definitions_path($c)
- Returns path to the canonical theme definitions JSON file
- Location: /root/static/config/theme_definitions.json

get_theme_mappings_path()
- Legacy method for compatibility
- Returns undef (mappings now read from theme_definitions.json)

get_theme_css_directory()
- Returns path to theme CSS directory
- Location: /root/static/css/themes

get_theme_definitions($c)
- Loads and parses theme definitions from JSON file
- Returns theme definitions hash or empty hash on error
- Includes comprehensive error handling with logging

get_all_themes($c)
- Returns all available theme definitions
- Loads from canonical theme_definitions.json file
- Provides comprehensive logging for debugging

get_site_theme($c, $site_name)
- NEW: Gets the theme for a specific site
- Parameters: Catalyst context object, site name string
- Returns: theme name string (defaults to 'default')
- Features:
  - Checks session cache first for performance
  - Uses site_themes mapping from JSON configuration
  - Case-insensitive site name matching
  - Validates theme exists in definitions
  - Caches result in session for future requests
  - Comprehensive logging for all decisions
  - Graceful error handling

Configuration Structure
The model reads from /root/static/config/theme_definitions.json with this structure:

{
  "themes": {
    "theme_name": {
      "name": "Display Name",
      "description": "Theme description",
      "variables": { ... CSS variables ... },
      "legacy_elements": { ... legacy CSS ... },
      "special_styles": { ... special styling ... }
    }
  },
  "site_themes": {
    "site_name": "theme_name",
    "default": "default",
    "csc": "csc",
    "usbm": "usbm"
  }
}

Session Integration
- Theme selections cached as session["theme_$site_name"]
- Improves performance by avoiding repeated JSON parsing
- Cache cleared when theme is explicitly changed

Error Handling
- JSON parsing errors logged and return default values
- Missing theme definitions default to 'default' theme
- File access errors handled gracefully
- All errors logged with file/line context

Dependencies
- Moose for object system
- JSON for configuration parsing
- File::Slurp for file operations
- Try::Tiny for error handling
- Comserv::Util::Logging for structured logging

Related Files
- Theme definitions: /root/static/config/theme_definitions.json
- Theme CSS files: /root/static/css/themes/
- Controller integration: /lib/Comserv/Controller/Root.pm (line 1120)

Usage Example
my $theme_name = $c->model('ThemeConfig')->get_site_theme($c, 'CSC');
# Returns 'csc' based on site_themes mapping
# Caches result in session for subsequent requests